# Styling with Tailwind

## Usage

- Prefer **Tailwind utility classes** in `className`; avoid inline `style` for layout and spacing
- Use breakpoints (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) for responsive design

## Custom Utilities (src/index.css)

- `.hero-gradient` — Hero background with overlay
- `.container-1440` — Max-width container with padding
- `.sidebar-active` — Active sidebar link (brand accent `#ec5b13`)

## Color Palette

- **Slate**: `slate-600`, `slate-900` for text; `slate-100`, `slate-200` for borders/bg
- **Brand accent**: `#ec5b13` (used in `.sidebar-active`)

## Example

```jsx
// BAD: Inline styles for layout
<div style={{ padding: "1rem", maxWidth: "1440px" }}>

// GOOD: Tailwind + custom utility
<div className="container-1440 px-4 py-6">
```
